reviewText: I liked the first twitches, and this one picks up where it left off! who wouldn't want to be a witch? and have 2 homes! fantasy is the way to go! if you love these two actresses, it's a must see. you can really see yourself there. of course, that's the whole point. has some good behind the scenes stuff too. always a plus. also if you have a disney acct you can add points to it through this dvd. good thing.

reviewText: I have watched everything these beautiful young ladies have been in.  I always enjoy their movies/shows but I couldn't barely get this one. A complete bore IMO.  The acting wasn't great either particularly by Tamera.  Tia was better.  The plot was just horrible.  Sorry girls.

reviewText: I like to watch this during Halloween, of course, just a cute movie that is family friendly and not too Disney sweet. Not too much else to say that hasn't been said already, I think, just that if you're looking for something to watch that isn't too scary/gross and you're an adult or an adult with kids that wants something that won't be too mind numbing, you might want to give this and it's predecessor a chance.

reviewText: Twitches too is such a good movie, I even think it's better than the first one.My favorite part was at the very end whenever Thantos was gone forever and Camerone and Alex had their dad back again - so sweet! Title: Twitches Too

reviewText: I literally grew up with Tia and Tamera, watching them on TV and in their movies.  When I saw this on Amazon, even as an adult, I bought this to add to my collection.  Tia and Tamera are wonderful in this "Teen Twin Witch" sequel.  Adventure takes them to new places as they learn to control their magic.  I enjoyed this movie and am glad to own it now, so that my niece (and maybe daughter some day!!) can watch this with me.
Title: Twitches Too
